{
  "texts": [
    "A frequency CNN (FCNN) is used in their technique to evaluate and categorize clean and counterfeit faces.",
    "To assess the efficacy of the FCNN, the FaceForensics + + dataset was employed.",
    "The study showed that FCNN detects forgeries efficiently in actual circumstances, including high and low video quality.",
    "Among all other facial modification techniques, the FCNN detects deepfakes with the greatest recall of 0.9256, 0.8639, and 0.8399 for raw, c23, and c40, respectively.",
    "Their technique was also tested on a CelebDF (v2) dataset as well as an automated FaceForensic benchmark."
  ]
}